Brogue-style Recursive Shadowcasting in Pure C  This is a generic, standalone C port of the FOV algorithm from Brian Walker's Brogue.  Most implementations I found were tied to specific map structures. This one uses a simple callback (RlcBlocksFunc) for obstruction checks, so you can drop it into any project (ECS, flat arrays, structs) without dependencies.  Features:      Recursive Shadowcasting (all 8 octants).      Correct LOS_SLOPE_GRANULARITY and fixed-point math from the original.      Optional "cautious walls" (lighting walls only if adjacent ground is visible).      Bonus: Generic Flood Fill and Distance Field functions.  Header-only friendly design (just .c and .h). Hope it saves someone the time of extracting it manually!
